o find out how much time is left.\n2. Once you have the days remaining, break the TOPIC down into logical sub-modules.\n3. Distribute these sub-modules over the available days.\n4. Output a clean, day-by-day schedule.\n5. Be encouraging and concise.\n\"\"\"\n\n# Initialize the Chat Session\n# FIX: We pass the function directly to 'tools'. The SDK handles the wrapping.\nchat = client.chats.create(\n    model=\"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n    config=GenerateContentConfig(\n        tools=[calculate_days_remaining], \n        system_instruction=system_instruction, \n        temperature=0.7, \n    )\n)\n\nprint(\"Agent initialized with Tools and Context.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-12-01T14:22:20.456411Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-12-01T14:22:20.456751Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-12-01T14:22:20.465308Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2025-12-01T14:22:20.456728Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-12-01T14:22:20.464308Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Agent initialized with Tools and Context.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# --- PART 3: The Interaction ---\n\n# The user prompt\nuser_prompt = \"I need to learn basic Python Programming. My exam is on 2025-12-20.\"\n\n# Send message to the agent\nresponse = chat.send_message(user_prompt)\n\n# Print the result\nprint(response.text)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-12-01T14:22:21.866559Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-12-01T14:22:21.866898Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-12-01T14:22:29.542907Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2025-12-01T14:22:21.866870Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-12-01T14:22:29.541946Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Great! You have 18 days to prepare. Here's a possible study schedule:\n\n*   **Day 1-3**: Introduction to Python & Basic Syntax (Variables, data types, operators)\n*   **Day 4-6**: Control Flow (If statements, loops - for/while)\n*   **Day 7-9**: Data Structures (Lists, tuples, 